The paper is about improving Neural Machine Translation (NMT) by incorporating syntactic information. This topic falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP), which is often classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new NMT model, which involves generating an arbitrary tree structure on the target side, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper uses experimental results to compare the performance of different methods, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with language translation, which could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as language translation is often used in image captioning tasks.
